{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Fortunately, dimensionality reduction is an effective approach to deal with this problem, which projects the training samples from the high-dimensional space to the low-dimensional subspace without losing of useful information.",
    "As a representative dimensionality reduction algorithm, principal component analysis (PCA) projects the training samples into the subspace spanned by several principal eigenvectors of the covariance matrix of the training samples [194].",
    "As an extension of PCA, kernel PCA uses the kernel trick to achieve nonlinear dimensionality reduction [195].",
    "In addition, the auto-encoder can train the neural network to learn the low-dimensional representation of the training data [198].",
    "RLRL has been widely used to handle the multi-step decision problems in a dynamic environment [196]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "As a representative dimensionality reduction algorithm, principal component analysis (PCA) projects the training samples into the subspace spanned by several principal eigenvectors of the covariance matrix of the training samples [194].",
